# Numpy for Systems of Equations
Use NumPy to solve 'x' and 'y' in the following linear algebra equations: 

$x+2y=5$

$3x+4y=7$

$$ 
\begin{bmatrix}
1 & 2 \\
3 & 4 \\
\end{bmatrix}
*
\begin{bmatrix}
-3 & 4 \\
\end{bmatrix}
=
\begin{bmatrix}
(1*-3) + (2*4) \\
(3*-3) + (4*4) \\
\end{bmatrix}
=
\begin{bmatrix}
(-3+8) \\
(-9+16) \\
\end{bmatrix}
=
\begin{bmatrix}
5 \\
7 \\
\end{bmatrix}
$$
